1
00:00:00,036 --> 00:00:04,074
Welcome to Essential Hayek
 欢迎来到哈耶克简要

2
00:00:04,074 --> 00:00:06,024
I'm Don Boudreaux
 我是Don Boudreaux

3
00:00:06,024 --> 00:00:09,004
professor of economics at George Mason University
 乔治梅森大学经济学教授

4
00:00:09,004 --> 00:00:11,022
senior fellow with the Fraser Institute
 弗雷泽研究所高级研究员

5
00:00:11,022 --> 00:00:13,036
and blogger at Café Hayek
 博客Café Hayek的博主之一

6
00:00:13,036 --> 00:00:16,022
This video was part of the Fraser Institute initiative
 本视频是由弗雷泽研究所制作的

7
00:00:16,022 --> 00:00:22,082
to present the key ideas of F.A. Hayek in an easily accessible format
 对哈耶克关键思想的通俗介绍

8
00:00:22,082 --> 00:00:26,050
In this video, we provide an overview of Hayek's life
 这个视频是关于哈耶克的生平、

9
00:00:26,050 --> 00:00:32,042
his accomplishments, and the events that influenced his thinking
 成就和影响他思想的事件

10
00:00:32,042 --> 00:00:36,086
Frederich A. Hayek was born in Vienna on May 8th, 1899
 弗雷德里希A.哈耶克于1899/5/8出生于维也纳

11
00:00:36,086 --> 00:00:42,020
As a young man, he served in the Austrian army during World War I
 年轻时他加入了奥匈帝国陆军并参加了一战

12
00:00:42,020 --> 00:00:45,018
Hayek soon found himself assigned to the Italian front
 他被分配到了意大利前线服役

13
00:00:45,018 --> 00:00:50,072
with his experience in combat had a profound and decisive influence on his life
 这段战争经历给哈耶克的一生带来了深远且决定性的影响

14
00:00:50,072 --> 00:00:53,046
Following the war, Hayek returned to Vienna
 战争结束后，哈耶克返回了维也纳

15
00:00:53,046 --> 00:00:58,020
and completed doctoral degrees in both law and political science
 并获得了法律和政治学两个博士学位

16
00:00:58,020 --> 00:01:01,036
Working as a young economist in Austria in the late 1920s
 1920年代后期，哈耶克作为奥地利年轻的经济学家

17
00:01:01,036 --> 00:01:05,020
Hayek was taken under the wing of noted economist Ludwig von Mises
 在知名经济学家路德维希·冯·米塞斯的羽翼下成长

18
00:01:05,020 --> 00:01:08,050
and began his work researching business cycles
 并开始了对于经济周期的研究

19
00:01:08,050 --> 00:01:12,042
Business cycles, or what were then called trade cycles
 经济周期，后来亦叫商业周期

20
00:01:12,042 --> 00:01:15,088
are known today as booms and recessions
 今天被人们称作景气和衰退

21
00:01:15,088 --> 00:01:18,072
In 1931, Hayek moved to England
 1931年，哈耶克移居英国

22
00:01:18,072 --> 00:01:21,086
and joined the faculty of the London School of Economics
 于伦敦政治经济学院任教

23
00:01:21,086 --> 00:01:24,010
With his research into booms and recessions
 在1930年代大萧条的背景下

24
00:01:24,010 --> 00:01:31,062
led to his growing fame, especially against the backdrop of the Great Depression of the 1930s
 他对于经济周期的研究，使他声望日隆

25
00:01:31,062 --> 00:01:32,084
During this time
 在这期间

26
00:01:32,084 --> 00:01:36,020
Hayek crossed path with his greatest intellectual rival
 哈耶克遇上了他智力上最重要的对手

27
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,094
John Maynard Keynes
 约翰·梅纳德·凯恩斯

28
00:01:37,094 --> 00:01:44,060
who promoted the idea that governments could actively and successfully manage the economy
 凯恩斯推广了政府可以积极、成功地调控经济的理念

29
00:01:44,060 --> 00:01:46,060
Hayek argued in contrast
 哈耶克则持相反观点

30
00:01:46,060 --> 00:01:48,042
that an economy is too complicated
 他认为经济太过复杂

31
00:01:48,042 --> 00:01:51,078
and the information needed to make decisions too decentralized
 决策所需的信息也太过分散

32
00:01:51,078 --> 00:01:56,044
for a centrally planned economy to be efficient or effective
 使得中央计划经济无法有效运转

33
00:01:56,047 --> 00:01:59,030
Eventually, most economists and policymakers
 最终，大多数经济学家和政治决策者

34
00:01:59,030 --> 00:02:02,034
embraced Keynes' view of the world and the role of government
 选择拥抱凯恩斯对于世界和政府角色的看法

35
00:02:02,034 --> 00:02:06,084
which came to dominate economics thinking for the next forty years
 这一潮流延续了四十年

36
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:11,034
Hayek was largely relegated to the sidelines
 哈耶克则在很大程度上被主流经济学界遗忘了

37
00:02:11,034 --> 00:02:13,076
But Hayek's time in the shadows was brief
 不过哈耶克并未在阴影中待太久

38
00:02:13,076 --> 00:02:15,076
In 1944
 1944年

39
00:02:15,076 --> 00:02:18,088
he published the classic volume, <The Road to Serfdom>
 他出版了经典之作——《通往奴役之路》

40
00:02:18,088 --> 00:02:21,046
which became a bestseller
 该书也成了畅销书

41
00:02:21,046 --> 00:02:25,008
In 1950, Hayek moved to the University of Chicago
 1950年，哈耶克前往芝加哥大学任教

42
00:02:25,008 --> 00:02:26,096
where he published his second major work
 在那他出版了他的第二部重要著作

43
00:02:26,096 --> 00:02:29,048
<The Constitution of Liberty>
 《自由秩序原理》

44
00:02:29,048 --> 00:02:33,094
Subsequent years would see the publication of two more big thick books
 在之后的日子里他又出版了另外两本大部头

45
00:02:33,094 --> 00:02:37,052
the three-volume <Law, Legislation and Liberty>
 三卷本的《法律、立法与自由》

46
00:02:37,052 --> 00:02:41,028
and, in 1988, <The Fatal Conceit>
 和1988年出版的《致命的自负》

47
00:02:41,028 --> 00:02:45,060
In 1974, Hayek was awarded the Nobel prize in Economics
 1974年，哈耶克被授予诺贝尔经济学奖

48
00:02:45,060 --> 00:02:51,072
finally earning the professional acclaim that he’d lost with his refusal to jump onto Keynesian bandwagon
 终于重获因当年与凯恩斯意见不同而失去的专业声誉

49
00:02:51,072 --> 00:02:53,024
In 1991
 1991年

50
00:02:53,024 --> 00:02:57,048
the collapse of the Soviet Union provided further indication of Hayek's notion
 苏联的解体为哈耶克关于

51
00:02:57,048 --> 00:03:02,024
that central planning by government simply does not, indeed, cannot, work
 政府中央计划经济无法、也不可能运转的见解提供了新的注脚

52
00:03:02,024 --> 00:03:05,048
Readers interested in exploring Hayek's theories in greater depth
 我们鼓励想更深入了解哈耶克理论的读者

53
00:03:05,048 --> 00:03:08,024
are encouraged to read his works directly
 直接阅读哈耶克的著作

54
00:03:08,024 --> 00:03:10,098
I recommend starting with <The Road to Serfdom>
 我建议从《通往奴役之路》开始

55
00:03:10,098 --> 00:03:15,028
and economic students might wish to start with Hayek's influential 1945 essay
 经济系学生可能会希望从哈耶克1945年那篇极富影响力的文章

56
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:18,046
<The Use of Knowledge in Society>
 《知识在社会中的运用》开始

57
